[Nouns] synchronism; coexistence, coincidence; simultaneousness, simultaneity; concurrence, concomitance, unity of time, interim.
[Having equal times] isochronism.
contemporary, coetanian.
[Verbs] coexist, concur, accompany, go hand in hand, keep pace with; synchronize.
[Adjectives] synchronous, synchronal, synchronical, synchronistical; simultaneous, coexisting, coincident, concomitant, concurrent; coeval, coevous; contemporary, contemporaneous; coetaneous; coeternal; isochronous.
[Adverbs] at the same time; simultaneously; together, in concert, during the same time; in the same breath; pari passu; in the interim.
at the very moment [more]; just as, as soon as; meanwhile (while) [more].
